260
00:14:09,215 --> 00:14:11,650
and I'm not done kicking their sorry asses yet.

261
00:14:12,117 --> 00:14:15,120
I also have a few things I'd like to say to Sensei.

262
00:14:15,154 --> 00:14:17,656
- [soft music] - I have some things to say too.

263
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:20,092
How long will you need to beat him up to feel better?

264
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:23,162
[footsteps pattering]

265
00:14:25,164 --> 00:14:26,632
[Gintoki laughs]

266
00:14:26,665 --> 00:14:29,168
[music continues]

267
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:35,174
[all] An eternity of beatings would not be long enough!

268
00:14:35,674 --> 00:14:38,177
[music continues]

269
00:14:44,450 --> 00:14:46,252
- [gasps] - [gun firing]

270
00:14:46,285 --> 00:14:47,553
[Katsura grunts]

271
00:14:47,586 --> 00:14:49,555
[bomb explodes]

272
00:14:55,194 --> 00:14:56,195
Zura!

273
00:14:57,162 --> 00:14:59,598
- [Katsura groaning] - [footsteps thumping]

274
00:15:07,206 --> 00:15:09,475
[ray gun zapping]

275
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:14,046
[man over speaker] To those occupying the Terminal,

276
00:15:14,713 --> 00:15:17,549
you are completely surrounded.

277
00:15:18,484 --> 00:15:21,053
Resistance is futile.

278
00:15:21,620 --> 00:15:23,522
Give yourselves up now!

279
00:15:24,657 --> 00:15:26,325
If you refuse--

280
00:15:26,358 --> 00:15:28,093
Shoot them all down!

281
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:29,595
[explosion rumbling]

282
00:15:29,628 --> 00:15:31,664
[ray guns zapping]

283
00:15:31,697 --> 00:15:34,533
[man over speaker] Uh, if you refuse,

284
00:15:35,334 --> 00:15:37,469
let me express my gratitude.

285
00:15:38,237 --> 00:15:39,672
It is thanks to you all

286
00:15:40,139 --> 00:15:44,610
that our country has become so damn strong!

287
00:15:44,643 --> 00:15:47,246
[upbeat music]

288
00:15:52,651 --> 00:15:55,387
[men shouting]

289
00:16:03,262 --> 00:16:04,530
Those freaky guys.

290
00:16:05,097 --> 00:16:06,098
Let's go!

291
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:10,002
It has been many long decades

292
00:16:10,202 --> 00:16:12,538
since you last came to Earth, Amanto.

293
00:16:12,571 --> 00:16:16,775
We've lived! Lived full of doubt and agony!

294
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:19,378
But now we can say this,

295
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:22,114
those days have not been in vain!

296
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:25,017
- [grunts] - [man groans]

297
00:16:25,417 --> 00:16:26,518
[shouts]

298
00:16:26,719 --> 00:16:29,221
Amidst all that we have lost,

299
00:16:29,254 --> 00:16:30,789
we have found which is important,

300
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:32,791
that which we must protect!

301
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:34,593
[music continues]

302
00:16:34,626 --> 00:16:36,261
Our shadows on the ground

303
00:16:36,295 --> 00:16:39,098
have shown us the way to the light and here to you!

304
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:45,304
You don't scare us, not anymore.

305
00:16:46,305 --> 00:16:50,175
We are going to take you all head on! Face to ugly face!

306
00:16:50,476 --> 00:16:51,710
[music continues]

307
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:55,147
[all grunting]

308
00:16:58,717 --> 00:17:02,788
[both] Huh! Welcome to the land of samurai.

309
00:17:02,821 --> 00:17:04,189
[music continues]

310
00:17:05,791 --> 00:17:06,792
Huh?

311
00:17:07,726 --> 00:17:09,728
A land whose people have minds of steel.

312
00:17:10,462 --> 00:17:13,465
And a land whose people possess souls of silver.

313
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:16,702
[both] We're glad you could pop by!

314
00:17:16,735 --> 00:17:18,570
[men groaning]

315
00:17:19,471 --> 00:17:21,774
[music continues]

316
00:17:22,741 --> 00:17:24,576
[gun firing]

317
00:17:34,286 --> 00:17:37,122
[ray gun zapping]

318
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:40,726
[bell dinging]

319
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:42,361
Gintoki!

320
00:17:42,628 --> 00:17:44,730
[footsteps thumping]

321
00:17:44,763 --> 00:17:46,865
[guns firing]

322
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,534
- Gintoki! - Huh?

323
00:17:50,335 --> 00:17:52,371
[bomb explodes]

324
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:54,873
[gun firing]

325
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,475
[bomb explodes]

326
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,111
[Kondo] Hey Pops! Little help down here!

327
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:01,747
We need to split up the enemy's defenses

328
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:02,748
surrounding the Terminal!

329
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:06,485
Yeah that sounds like some tedious crap to me.

330
00:18:06,518 --> 00:18:09,354
We'll just attack the mother -scratchin' mothership up top!

331
00:18:09,388 --> 00:18:12,458
[Kondo over radio] Um, right now, that ship contains all the Altana

332
00:18:12,491 --> 00:18:14,126
it has already taken from the Terminal!

333
00:18:14,393 --> 00:18:16,295
If we launch an attack it now,

334
00:18:16,328 --> 00:18:17,529
no telling what will happen.

335
00:18:17,863 --> 00:18:19,431
So ix-nay on the help.

336
00:18:19,465 --> 00:18:21,700
[man grunts]

337
00:18:21,733 --> 00:18:23,669
[upbeat music]

338
00:18:26,238 --> 00:18:28,373
Yo. You took you your sweet ass time.

339
00:18:28,674 --> 00:18:31,477
You took so long, I thought you guys [grunts]

340
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:32,778
got scared and run away.

341
00:18:33,345 --> 00:18:35,647
You can't have a party without the guests of honor.

342
00:18:35,914 --> 00:18:38,183
[grunts] Know what I mean?

343
00:18:38,217 --> 00:18:41,353
Well, well, so you finally admit

344
00:18:41,386 --> 00:18:43,689
the Odd Jobs are better than you, huh?

345
00:18:44,523 --> 00:18:46,258
The hell are you talking about?

346
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:48,227
I'm just saying, if we're gonna raise a little hell,

347
00:18:48,694 --> 00:18:51,797
it's more fun to do it with the nastiest devils around.

348
00:18:52,431 --> 00:18:53,799
And you guys are nasty.

349
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:57,302
So I guess that would mean we're out, then, huh?

350
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,405
[music continues]

351
00:19:00,873 --> 00:19:04,409
Let's get going. Let's go see our guests of honor.

352
00:19:06,545 --> 00:19:08,514
And raise hell one last time!

353
00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:12,251
[ominous music]

354
00:19:12,284 --> 00:19:14,820
[alien] This is shaping up to be a long, drawn-out battle.

355
00:19:15,387 --> 00:19:17,389
We should fall back and regroup.

356
00:19:17,422 --> 00:19:19,658
Even if we're able to revive Utsuro,

357
00:19:19,691 --> 00:19:22,327
it would be for naught if we lost the Sect in the process.

358
00:19:22,694 --> 00:19:25,364
We would lose the ability to produce the elixir

359
00:19:25,397 --> 00:19:27,833
and thus our chance to return to power.

360
00:19:27,866 --> 00:19:31,803
There is no need to worry. Everything is going as planned.

361
00:19:32,471 --> 00:19:34,706
It truly does appear as though Utsuro

362
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:37,309
can only be fueled by the Altana of Earth.

363
00:19:37,743 --> 00:19:41,480
Just look! Our god is truly pleased!

364
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:46,385
He's absorbing Altana.

365
00:19:46,418 --> 00:19:47,719
I'm not sure I understand.

366
00:19:47,753 --> 00:19:49,855
Is it actually reconstructing his heart?

367
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:51,890
Time is nigh.

368
00:19:52,457 --> 00:19:53,625
Soon my friends,

369
00:19:55,427 --> 00:19:56,862
our god will awaken.

370
00:19:57,396 --> 00:19:58,964
Is it not enough by now?

371
00:19:58,997 --> 00:20:00,699
Prolonging any further will make it

372
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:02,367
more difficult for us to leave.

373
00:20:02,734 --> 00:20:04,336
Prepare to withdraw!

374
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,506
[both groaning]

375
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:13,545
You have no control of your bodies.

376
00:20:14,012 --> 00:20:15,647
It happened to me as well.

377
00:20:16,982 --> 00:20:20,786
We Tendoshu self-destructed by stealing Utsuro's blood,

378
00:20:21,820 --> 00:20:24,790
but that very same blood also brought us back.

379
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:29,928
We were being kept alive, we were being used.

380
00:20:30,362 --> 00:20:31,763
[ominous music]

381
00:20:31,797 --> 00:20:33,966
We were controlled by his genes.

382
00:20:33,999 --> 00:20:36,802
Taken from the very moment that we took them in.

383
00:20:37,536 --> 00:20:40,272
[both groaning]

384
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:46,979
We've always been a part of Utsuro,

385
00:20:48,347 --> 00:20:52,818
and now it falls upon us to execute his will.

386
00:20:57,823 --> 00:21:00,325
[soft music]

387
00:21:19,611 --> 00:21:21,580
[music continues]

388
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:38,430
[Takasugi] Give up the heart.

389
00:21:38,864 --> 00:21:41,733
Such treasures do not belong in your hands.

390
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,336
They are meant to hold better things.

391
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:47,773
[soft music]

392
00:21:47,806 --> 00:21:49,474
[Gintoki] Since we had the same teacher,

393
00:21:50,609 --> 00:21:52,611
we were fated to cross swords.

394
00:21:56,682 --> 00:21:59,651
If I could do it all over again, I...

395
00:22:01,953 --> 00:22:03,755
I would have loved to be one of you.

396
00:22:06,825 --> 00:22:08,593
[Takasugi] I have my own things,

397
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:12,597
and you have your own things to take back, yes?

398
00:22:15,033 --> 00:22:16,601
[metal clanking]

399
00:22:17,469 --> 00:22:19,571
Takasugi, listen I...

400
00:22:19,604 --> 00:22:21,006
[explosion rumbles]

401
00:22:21,039 --> 00:22:23,008
[elevator dinging]

402
00:22:24,776 --> 00:22:27,913
[guns firing]

403
00:22:30,148 --> 00:22:31,750
[door creaking]

404
00:22:31,783 --> 00:22:33,919
[blood dipping]

405
00:22:36,621 --> 00:22:38,056
[door banging]

406
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:41,493
[bomb beeping]

407
00:22:42,728 --> 00:22:45,464
[bomb explodes]

408
00:22:49,768 --> 00:22:50,802
Let's get a move on.

409
00:22:54,806 --> 00:22:55,807
Takasugi.

410
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:57,275
Yeah?

411
00:22:57,309 --> 00:23:00,045
There's nothing left for me to take back anymore.

412
00:23:00,078 --> 00:23:01,113
Everything is done.

413
00:23:03,682 --> 00:23:07,919
Whatever I have lost, somehow, it has come back to me.

414
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:11,790
It's all right here and I'm here to make sure

415
00:23:11,823 --> 00:23:13,959
that I don't lose any of it ever again.

416
00:23:21,099 --> 00:23:22,734
- [explosion rumbles] - [both grunting]

417
00:23:22,768 --> 00:23:25,003
Gintoki! Takasugi!

418
00:23:26,738 --> 00:23:27,973
- [Katsura groans] - [Gintoki] Zura!

419
00:23:28,940 --> 00:23:29,975
Hang on, okay!

420
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:33,712
Now!

421
00:23:34,546 --> 00:23:36,448
[explosion rumbles]

422
00:23:43,054 --> 00:23:44,489
- [Gintoki] You're stepping on me. - Huh?

423
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:47,092
[Gintoki] Now we're even.

424
00:23:48,727 --> 00:23:51,229
You're the last person I wanna owe anything.

425
00:23:51,263 --> 00:23:53,999
What a coincidence, I could say the sa-- [groans]

426
00:23:57,736 --> 00:23:59,871
[dramatic music]

427
00:24:00,605 --> 00:24:01,740
[Gintoki] Takasugi.

428
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:03,775
[Takasugi groans]

429
00:24:07,712 --> 00:24:09,247
- [Gintoki growls] - It's over.

430
00:24:09,281 --> 00:24:11,483
You people cannot defeat me.

431
00:24:11,817 --> 00:24:13,752
[music continues]

432
00:24:16,721 --> 00:24:19,724
Did you see it, the Utsuro that lives within me?

433
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:22,093
[Gintoki groans]

434
00:24:23,862 --> 00:24:26,264
Utsuro rules over and decides for all.

435
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:30,635
His designs are inescapable. He is our fate.

436
00:24:31,703 --> 00:24:33,004
[swords clanking]

437
00:24:33,738 --> 00:24:35,507
[music continues]

438
00:24:38,009 --> 00:24:39,277
[Takasugi] Is that so?

439
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:40,779
Then what you're telling me,

440
00:24:42,013 --> 00:24:44,049
is that the only reason I'm standing here in front of you

441
00:24:44,082 --> 00:24:47,919
and totally not dead, is because it is the will of Utsuro?

442
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:51,156
I don't think so. Oh, no.

443
00:24:51,656 --> 00:24:53,058
We weren't led here by anyone.

444
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:55,627
We are here of our own free will.

445
00:24:56,228 --> 00:24:58,797
[music continues]

446
00:25:03,034 --> 00:25:05,670
[bombs explode]

447
00:25:06,972 --> 00:25:08,607
[music continues]

448
00:25:14,279 --> 00:25:15,947
[swords clanking]

449
00:25:19,951 --> 00:25:21,853
[men panting]

450
00:25:22,654 --> 00:25:23,822
Go! Now!

451
00:25:24,222 --> 00:25:26,892
[music continues]

452
00:25:29,794 --> 00:25:31,029
[swords clanking]

453
00:25:32,964 --> 00:25:34,933
I am taking this back.

454
00:25:35,934 --> 00:25:37,235
[ray gun zapping]

455
00:25:42,674 --> 00:25:43,775
[Katsura grunts]

456
00:25:49,114 --> 00:25:49,915
[metal clanking]

457
00:25:51,249 --> 00:25:53,952
You are Hitsugi, isn't that correct?

458
00:25:54,753 --> 00:25:57,689
One of the three crows in the Tenshoin Naraku.

459
00:25:58,223 --> 00:25:59,624
Why would you go this far?

460
00:26:00,959 --> 00:26:03,595
Why do you want the heart of your former chief, Utsuro, so badly?

461
00:26:05,230 --> 00:26:07,332
- [shouts] - [ray gun zapping]

462
00:26:07,365 --> 00:26:08,967
[upbeat music]

463
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,603
[Katsura grunts]

464
00:26:14,005 --> 00:26:15,674
[ray gun zapping]

465
00:26:18,143 --> 00:26:20,011
[ray gun zapping]

466
00:26:25,050 --> 00:26:26,685
[explosion rumbles]

467
00:26:27,018 --> 00:26:29,721
[music continues]

468
00:26:31,022 --> 00:26:32,123
[grunting]

469
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:37,729
[Katsura groans]

470
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:40,031
[music continues]

471
00:26:43,335 --> 00:26:45,337
[Katsura groans]

472
00:26:46,171 --> 00:26:48,907
[Hitsugi] Give me the heart.

473
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:50,175
[Katsura groans]

474
00:26:53,778 --> 00:26:55,814
[grunting]

475
00:26:59,184 --> 00:27:00,185
[Katsura groans]

476
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:04,022
[shouts]

477
00:27:04,055 --> 00:27:06,891
[swords clanking]

478
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:09,661
[music continues]

479
00:27:17,335 --> 00:27:20,205
[swords clanking]

480
00:27:24,476 --> 00:27:27,679
[building rumbling]

481
00:27:29,214 --> 00:27:30,315
[grunting]

482
00:27:30,348 --> 00:27:31,683
[Hitsugi groans]

483
00:27:32,183 --> 00:27:33,818
[building rumbling]

484
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:37,088
Kagura! No!

485
00:27:37,522 --> 00:27:40,759
[building rumbling]

486
00:27:43,962 --> 00:27:45,363
- [Kagura groans] - I'm coming.

487
00:27:46,364 --> 00:27:49,701
Never mind me Shinpachi. Go on ahead! [groans]

488
00:27:49,934 --> 00:27:51,836
[music continues]

489
00:28:08,987 --> 00:28:11,222
[rocks thudding]

490
00:28:13,158 --> 00:28:15,193
[Hitsugi groans]

491
00:28:16,261 --> 00:28:17,729
Give me...

492
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:19,898
the heart!

493
00:28:21,166 --> 00:28:22,367
What's it for?

494
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:25,236
Naraku has already fallen apart. It is over.

495
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:27,272
[swords clanking]

496
00:28:27,872 --> 00:28:29,941
And yet you still want to bring Utsuro back,

497
00:28:29,974 --> 00:28:32,877
even if you have to reduce Edo to rubble in the process.

498
00:28:33,244 --> 00:28:34,279
[swords clanking]

499
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:37,982
[Katsura grunts]

500
00:28:40,418 --> 00:28:43,021
[explosion rumbling]

501
00:28:49,027 --> 00:28:50,295
The only one...

502
00:28:50,528 --> 00:28:54,532
The only one who can save him is me!

503
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:56,167
- [metal clanking] - [grunts]

504
00:29:05,009 --> 00:29:07,178
[electricity crackling]

505
00:29:13,618 --> 00:29:15,053
Wait, are you...

506
00:29:16,321 --> 00:29:17,455
Don't tell me.

507
00:29:24,295 --> 00:29:26,464
[electricity crackling]

508
00:29:30,869 --> 00:29:33,204
- [dramatic music] - [Takasugi groans]

509
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,076
[Gintoki grunting]

510
00:29:39,511 --> 00:29:40,512
[Gintoki gasps]

511
00:29:41,079 --> 00:29:42,480
[Gintoki groans]

512
00:29:47,152 --> 00:29:48,987
[ominous music]

513
00:29:49,921 --> 00:29:51,556
- You okay? - Make good use of me.

514
00:29:51,589 --> 00:29:53,324
Huh? What are you saying?

515
00:29:54,192 --> 00:29:57,095
[swords clanking]

516
00:30:03,501 --> 00:30:05,303
[glass shattering]

517
00:30:12,110 --> 00:30:14,312
[both screaming]

518
00:30:14,612 --> 00:30:16,481
[all thudding]

519
00:30:16,514 --> 00:30:19,250
[ominous music]

520
00:30:23,655 --> 00:30:25,190
It is futile.

521
00:30:25,223 --> 00:30:27,258
You will never be able to take us down,

522
00:30:27,625 --> 00:30:29,394
not with your inferior blood.

523
00:30:31,629 --> 00:30:33,097
[Takasugi whimpers]

524
00:30:33,131 --> 00:30:35,099
[ominous music]

525
00:30:38,002 --> 00:30:41,272
[Takasugi] Then let's go ahead and see whose blood, mine or yours,

526
00:30:41,639 --> 00:30:44,375
will end up draining out of our bodies first.

527
00:30:44,409 --> 00:30:46,277
It could go down to the wire.

528
00:30:47,512 --> 00:30:49,414
[ominous music]

529
00:30:50,281 --> 00:30:51,282
Yes. Do it.

530
00:30:54,385 --> 00:30:56,221
[explosion rumbles]

