[explosion rumbles]

795
00:46:20,077 --> 00:46:22,980
[glass shattering]

796
00:46:26,483 --> 00:46:28,285
[building rumbling]

797
00:46:28,318 --> 00:46:30,354
[Gintoki] Shinpachi! Kagura!

798
00:46:32,890 --> 00:46:35,025
[shouts] Goddammit!

799
00:46:35,058 --> 00:46:37,494
[panting]

800
00:47:05,255 --> 00:47:07,591
[ominous music]

801
00:47:22,239 --> 00:47:25,042
Two years ago, young Gintoki,

802
00:47:25,075 --> 00:47:27,110
as you decided to reject me,

803
00:47:27,544 --> 00:47:29,479
I believe I gave you some advice.

804
00:47:30,247 --> 00:47:31,515
So long as you live,

805
00:47:31,548 --> 00:47:34,184
tragedy and misery will continue.

806
00:47:34,218 --> 00:47:36,520
I can hear his voice very clearly.

807
00:47:38,322 --> 00:47:40,157
It says he wants to put an end,

808
00:47:41,225 --> 00:47:42,192
[chuckles]

809
00:47:43,126 --> 00:47:45,028
to anything and everything.

810
00:47:46,496 --> 00:47:48,599
[Gintoki] Yeah? Well, I couldn't agree more.

811
00:47:50,300 --> 00:47:51,568
Let's end this.

812
00:47:55,072 --> 00:47:56,273
With our swords.

813
00:47:57,007 --> 00:47:59,576
You still carry that little twig? [chuckles]

814
00:48:00,177 --> 00:48:02,312
[Utsuro groans]

815
00:48:10,053 --> 00:48:11,054
[Gintoki groans]

816
00:48:11,722 --> 00:48:14,024
[Utsuro laughs]

817
00:48:14,057 --> 00:48:16,360
[Gintoki groans]

818
00:48:17,194 --> 00:48:19,930
[rumbling]

819
00:48:28,605 --> 00:48:29,606
[Utsuro gasps]

820
00:48:30,807 --> 00:48:35,512
[Gintoki] Utsuro, we may have to put several of these twigs

821
00:48:35,545 --> 00:48:38,348
together to do it, but we will take back

822
00:48:38,382 --> 00:48:40,050
what we lost that day.

823
00:48:40,717 --> 00:48:43,387
That's a promise, I swear to you.

824
00:48:44,054 --> 00:48:45,055
- [grunts] - [blade slices]

825
00:48:49,092 --> 00:48:50,594
[ground rumbling]

826
00:48:53,263 --> 00:48:54,965
[swords clanking]

827
00:48:56,099 --> 00:48:59,636
Your little promise was broken along time ago,

828
00:49:00,337 --> 00:49:04,107
by the very man you foolishly call your friend.

829
00:49:04,608 --> 00:49:07,077
[wind whistling]

830
00:49:09,746 --> 00:49:13,216
Utsuro, no matter what number of tragedies

831
00:49:13,250 --> 00:49:15,218
may forever fall on that man,

832
00:49:15,585 --> 00:49:17,220
he is not the type of person

833
00:49:17,254 --> 00:49:19,356
to ever say he wants to end things.

834
00:49:20,590 --> 00:49:24,127
You know what he's more likely to say at times like these?

835
00:49:25,262 --> 00:49:28,165
Oh, he knows, I will simply destroy

836
00:49:28,765 --> 00:49:32,135
this rotten festering world you walk so freely upon.

837
00:49:32,536 --> 00:49:34,771
You know a place where you don't belong.

838
00:49:35,539 --> 00:49:36,740
[Utsuro gasps]

839
00:49:41,278 --> 00:49:43,013
- [gasps] - [ominous music]

840
00:49:46,650 --> 00:49:48,518
[Utsuro groans]

841
00:49:48,552 --> 00:49:50,020
[blood spatters]

842
00:49:55,559 --> 00:49:58,295
[ominous music]

843
00:50:11,308 --> 00:50:16,480
Utsuro, you are not alone. You are not the only one here.

844
00:50:24,221 --> 00:50:27,324
[footsteps thumping]

845
00:50:29,726 --> 00:50:31,461
Where is Shoyo's corpse?

846
00:50:32,295 --> 00:50:35,098
I wanna see his lifeless body before me.

847
00:50:37,734 --> 00:50:38,735
[Gintoki] A corpse?

848
00:50:39,669 --> 00:50:41,571
There was never one here to begin with.

849
00:50:48,578 --> 00:50:53,784
The one body lying flat on the ground was you, Utsuro.

850
00:50:55,352 --> 00:50:57,220
[ominous music]

851
00:51:08,732 --> 00:51:13,437
My Sensei, as much of a problem student I was,

852
00:51:13,470 --> 00:51:15,772
it seems I had some homework left to do.

853
00:51:17,541 --> 00:51:18,575
Go.

854
00:51:19,743 --> 00:51:23,647
Don't worry. You have many more students.

855
00:51:25,382 --> 00:51:26,883
Many more than just us.

856
00:51:26,917 --> 00:51:27,818
[Kagura groans]

857
00:51:27,851 --> 00:51:30,120
- [explosion rumbles] - [Kagura screams]

858
00:51:34,424 --> 00:51:36,626
- [Sadaharu growling] - [Shinpachi gasps]

859
00:51:39,496 --> 00:51:43,366
[Utsuro] I'll leave you to them and them to you.

860
00:51:44,768 --> 00:51:46,136
[all gasp]

861
00:51:49,406 --> 00:51:50,407
[Utsuro groaning]

862
00:51:51,508 --> 00:51:52,642
[Gintoki] You aren't some immortal demon anymore.

863
00:51:54,277 --> 00:51:57,547
The moment you entered his body, you were done for.

864
00:51:59,683 --> 00:52:02,919
I will put an end to you just like you wish, Utsuro.

865
00:52:02,953 --> 00:52:05,689
And also, I'll end your pathetic sob story.

866
00:52:05,922 --> 00:52:08,692
You think you have the ability to kill me?

867
00:52:09,559 --> 00:52:11,661
You wanted to save him, did you not?

868
00:52:11,695 --> 00:52:13,697
Wanted to protect him, I know you did.

869
00:52:14,664 --> 00:52:16,433
I learned that fact all too well

870
00:52:16,466 --> 00:52:18,235
during our travels to get here.

871
00:52:18,869 --> 00:52:21,538
If you kill your master for your friends,

872
00:52:21,571 --> 00:52:23,807
and then kill your friend for your master,

873
00:52:23,840 --> 00:52:25,475
what will that leave you with?

874
00:52:26,943 --> 00:52:27,944
Nothing.

875
00:52:28,845 --> 00:52:30,914
You will be nothing but a hollow void.

876
00:52:34,684 --> 00:52:36,653
Do you have what it takes to survive

877
00:52:36,686 --> 00:52:39,289
through such dark emptiness? [grunts]

878
00:52:50,800 --> 00:52:54,337
Utsuro, I will never be empty inside.

879
00:52:54,971 --> 00:52:55,972
[grunts]

880
00:52:57,707 --> 00:52:58,875
[swords clanking]

881
00:53:02,879 --> 00:53:05,815
[Gintoki] What I wanted to protect is right here with me.

882
00:53:06,850 --> 00:53:08,218
With me in spirit.

883
00:53:09,319 --> 00:53:10,420
[Utsuro gasps]

884
00:53:10,453 --> 00:53:12,422
[Utsuro groans]

885
00:53:15,025 --> 00:53:17,894
[swords clanking]

886
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:34,911
[shouts]

887
00:53:36,379 --> 00:53:37,380
[Utsuro groans]

888
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:44,654
[blow thuds]

889
00:53:47,958 --> 00:53:49,659
[Gintoki screams]

890
00:53:56,333 --> 00:53:57,801
[blow thuds]

891
00:54:06,409 --> 00:54:09,279
[no audio]

892
00:54:20,624 --> 00:54:22,425
- [sword whooshing] - [blow thuds]

893
00:54:31,134 --> 00:54:33,003
[no audio]

894
00:54:43,480 --> 00:54:45,715
[sword whooshing]

895
00:54:47,584 --> 00:54:48,752
[Utsuro groans]

896
00:54:48,785 --> 00:54:49,886
[blow thuds]

897
00:54:51,521 --> 00:54:52,822
[Gintoki shouts]

898
00:54:58,428 --> 00:54:59,729
[Utsuro sighs]

899
00:55:04,734 --> 00:55:07,337
Humans beings are hollow,

900
00:55:07,804 --> 00:55:10,040
but because they know that fact,

901
00:55:10,073 --> 00:55:12,642
they take root in the hearts of others,

902
00:55:12,676 --> 00:55:15,945
never fading, even after death has come for them,

903
00:55:16,880 --> 00:55:20,583
and therefore, continue to live on forever.

904
00:55:22,752 --> 00:55:24,788
[no audio]

905
00:55:25,689 --> 00:55:27,991
[wind blowing]

906
00:55:39,769 --> 00:55:40,870
[sword clanking]

907
00:55:47,911 --> 00:55:52,649
[Takasugi] The score is now 246 to 247,

908
00:55:53,483 --> 00:55:54,851
and you know what?

909
00:55:54,884 --> 00:55:57,020
I wouldn't have it any other way either.

910
00:55:57,554 --> 00:55:59,122
How the mighty have fallen, huh?

911
00:55:59,923 --> 00:56:01,458
In our final duel,

912
00:56:01,658 --> 00:56:05,128
I let someone else fight in my stead and lost.

913
00:56:06,596 --> 00:56:08,932
It was your sword that finally took him down,

914
00:56:09,799 --> 00:56:12,035
and the one who protected Shoyo and me,

915
00:56:12,068 --> 00:56:14,537
was you, it was all you.

916
00:56:14,938 --> 00:56:17,907
[chuckles] Nothing could feel any worse

917
00:56:17,941 --> 00:56:20,810
than a victory given to me out of pity from you.

918
00:56:22,946 --> 00:56:25,648
I couldn't make you, I couldn't force you

919
00:56:25,682 --> 00:56:27,417
to cut down Sensei again.

920
00:56:29,552 --> 00:56:31,421
Because, compared to him,

921
00:56:31,855 --> 00:56:34,057
I was a much easier target, wasn't I?

922
00:56:34,791 --> 00:56:35,825
Damn straight!

923
00:56:36,226 --> 00:56:37,994
There's no other face in the universe

924
00:56:38,027 --> 00:56:40,530
I enjoy punching as much as yours.

925
00:56:43,566 --> 00:56:46,102
- [gentle music] - It was the same when we were kids.

926
00:56:46,703 --> 00:56:48,838
We fought every time we met.

927
00:56:49,773 --> 00:56:51,975
I figured growing up some would fix that,

928
00:56:52,976 --> 00:56:56,212
but we remained competitive little brats the whole time.

929
00:56:57,080 --> 00:56:59,749
And in your case, you didn't even manage

930
00:56:59,783 --> 00:57:01,684
to grow out of being such a jerk.

931
00:57:01,985 --> 00:57:03,720
[Takasugi] Eat it, you asshole.

932
00:57:04,254 --> 00:57:05,555
[Gintoki chuckles]

933
00:57:07,023 --> 00:57:09,893
Maybe this is just how we were fated to end up all along, my friend.

934
00:57:10,927 --> 00:57:13,730
But hey, that's not too bad, is it?

935
00:57:15,598 --> 00:57:18,134
Takasugi, you know what?

936
00:57:19,235 --> 00:57:22,105
As much as we love to fight each other,

937
00:57:24,140 --> 00:57:25,241
that's not all.

938
00:57:25,275 --> 00:57:27,143
[music continues]

939
00:57:27,710 --> 00:57:29,746
We're so much more than that.

940
00:57:32,982 --> 00:57:35,585
I loved to get drunk with you just as much.

941
00:57:41,291 --> 00:57:43,827
[music continues]

942
00:57:45,128 --> 00:57:47,897
[chuckles] Yeah, no. That's not us.

943
00:57:48,631 --> 00:57:50,633
Instead of wasting time on drinks,

944
00:57:51,568 --> 00:57:53,102
I would've used it to beat your face in

945
00:57:53,136 --> 00:57:54,637
as many times as I could.

946
00:57:55,038 --> 00:57:56,039
[Gintoki chuckles]

947
00:57:58,007 --> 00:57:59,309
[music continues]

948
00:57:59,342 --> 00:58:02,512
But now, I guess, I'll have to give it a rest.

949
00:58:03,313 --> 00:58:04,581
You should get going.

950
00:58:06,783 --> 00:58:08,151
You aren't empty, you know.

951
00:58:08,785 --> 00:58:10,553
You still have plenty to protect.

952
00:58:14,657 --> 00:58:17,026
[music continues]

953
00:58:18,161 --> 00:58:19,195
Takasugi.

954
00:58:20,296 --> 00:58:21,297
[Takasugi] Gintoki,

955
00:58:22,799 --> 00:58:24,801
this crushed left eye of mine

956
00:58:26,035 --> 00:58:27,904
it closed forever on that day,

957
00:58:27,937 --> 00:58:29,739
with the last thing it saw etched

958
00:58:29,772 --> 00:58:31,174
into the back of its eyelid.

959
00:58:32,976 --> 00:58:36,045
I've lived my entire life looking at your gloomy

960
00:58:36,079 --> 00:58:38,815
pasty face and I gotta say, I'm sick of it.

961
00:58:40,650 --> 00:58:42,819
So at least when my other eye closes,

962
00:58:44,087 --> 00:58:47,123
don't go looking like a goddamn pouty pants again, all right.

963
00:58:47,657 --> 00:58:48,825
[crying]

964
00:58:50,326 --> 00:58:52,896
The cocky little kid who stood tall

965
00:58:52,929 --> 00:58:54,764
before me when we first met.

966
00:58:56,332 --> 00:58:58,234
The man I always wanted to best,

967
00:58:59,002 --> 00:59:01,271
the man I spent my whole life chasing,

968
00:59:02,705 --> 00:59:03,706
the man,

969
00:59:04,707 --> 00:59:06,843
that prematurely gray man,

970
00:59:07,777 --> 00:59:09,679
is so much better than that.

971
00:59:11,247 --> 00:59:12,715
Do you hear me?

972
00:59:15,018 --> 00:59:17,220
I... [sobs]

973
00:59:21,858 --> 00:59:24,994
Wait for me in hell, Takasugi, my old friend.

974
00:59:25,962 --> 00:59:28,064
You don't get to quit while you're ahead.

975
00:59:28,097 --> 00:59:29,999
I'll beat you for sure next time.

976
00:59:31,734 --> 00:59:33,102
Yeah, you wish.

977
00:59:37,340 --> 00:59:39,876
[music continues]

978
00:59:47,417 --> 00:59:49,352
[Gintoki crying]

979
01:00:09,939 --> 01:00:13,042
[electricity crackling]

980
01:00:34,964 --> 01:00:38,201
[machines beeping]

981
01:00:38,401 --> 01:00:42,005
Oh man! That ship sucked up way too much Altana!

982
01:00:42,905 --> 01:00:45,074
[creaking]

983
01:00:49,812 --> 01:00:52,448
I must say, I don't understand why you're helping me,

984
01:00:52,482 --> 01:00:55,351
I'm the direct cause of all this pain and tragedy.

985
01:00:55,852 --> 01:00:58,221
Whenever you see someone in need, you help them out

986
01:00:58,254 --> 01:00:59,589
and then run off with all their money.

987
01:00:59,622 --> 01:01:03,459
That's what Gintoki Sakata has always taught us over the years.

988
01:01:03,926 --> 01:01:07,063
And besides, I've always wanted to talk to the guy

989
01:01:07,096 --> 01:01:09,198
who made him the person who he is today.

990
01:01:10,366 --> 01:01:13,436
[Shoyo] I'm afraid it's the other way around.

991
01:01:14,837 --> 01:01:16,906
[soft music]

992
01:01:20,977 --> 01:01:22,378
If I had never met them,

993
01:01:22,945 --> 01:01:25,214
I would have remained as empty as Utsuro.

994
01:01:27,850 --> 01:01:30,820
They made... they made me human.

995
01:01:32,221 --> 01:01:34,357
[music continues]

996
01:01:41,097 --> 01:01:45,968
But, my mere existence only served to shackle them down,

997
01:01:46,002 --> 01:01:47,370
and keep them from growing.

998
01:01:48,504 --> 01:01:50,073
I have absolutely no right

999
01:01:50,106 --> 01:01:52,175
to dare call myself their teacher.

1000
01:01:52,208 --> 01:01:56,245
Yeah, well, even if everything you just said is true,

1001
01:01:56,279 --> 01:02:00,149
it's because of you that we got to meet Gintoki Sakata.

1002
01:02:00,850 --> 01:02:05,021
I've always wanted to meet you so I could tell you,

1003
01:02:06,289 --> 01:02:07,290
thank you.

1004
01:02:08,424 --> 01:02:09,425
Hm.

1005
01:02:11,027 --> 01:02:13,196
[Shinpachi] I'm sure Gin and the others feel the same way as me.

1006
01:02:13,429 --> 01:02:14,430
[radio static crackles]

1007
01:02:14,464 --> 01:02:17,533
[Katsura] Gintoki! Takasugi! It's me.

1008
01:02:17,567 --> 01:02:20,036
Can you hear me? Are you all right?

1009
01:02:21,037 --> 01:02:25,174
Listen, we've managed to taken over Kuyo, the enemy...

1010
01:02:25,208 --> 01:02:26,876
the enemy is in tatters, too,

1011
01:02:26,909 --> 01:02:29,512
but the Terminal is still running out of control.

1012
01:02:29,545 --> 01:02:31,047
It's only a matter of time before it

1013
01:02:31,080 --> 01:02:32,849
collapses along with this ship.

1014
01:02:32,882 --> 01:02:33,883
Get out of here at once!

1015
01:02:34,517 --> 01:02:36,319
Zura! Running away won't help!

1016
01:02:37,320 --> 01:02:39,222
Look, if the Terminal were to go down,

1017
01:02:39,255 --> 01:02:42,024
all the Altana inside of it will go completely berserk.

1018
01:02:42,058 --> 01:02:44,794
And if worse comes to worst, this entire planet could blow!

1019
01:02:45,294 --> 01:02:48,030
Okay, but there must be something we can do.

1020
01:02:48,064 --> 01:02:49,098
- [static crackles] - Uh--

1021
01:02:50,366 --> 01:02:53,302
I ask that you allow me to handle this situation.

1022
01:02:53,936 --> 01:02:56,205
Who the hell are you? [gasps]

1023
01:02:57,039 --> 01:02:59,208
I'll use the weapons on-board this ship.

1024
01:02:59,942 --> 01:03:02,178
I will fire all of the Altana and it's mine

1025
01:03:02,211 --> 01:03:04,080
back down via the Terminal.

1026
01:03:05,314 --> 01:03:08,084
And I'll do so by using the Altana within me.

1027
01:03:08,885 --> 01:03:12,054
But, even if that manages to quell its rage,

1028
01:03:12,088 --> 01:03:14,157
the Terminal will not be left standing.

1029
01:03:15,091 --> 01:03:16,559
My school's biggest prodigy,

1030
01:03:17,627 --> 01:03:20,029
can I ask you to handle the evacuations?

1031
01:03:21,297 --> 01:03:23,299
I have complete confidence in you.

1032
01:03:23,332 --> 01:03:26,102
I want you all to live on to the next adventure.

1033
01:03:26,135 --> 01:03:27,436
[static crackles]

1034
01:03:30,473 --> 01:03:32,208
All hands should evacuate!

1035
01:03:32,241 --> 01:03:35,011
We need to get out of the Terminal as soon as we can!

1036
01:03:35,478 --> 01:03:37,547
[man] Zura! Feel free to use our ships!

1037
01:03:38,381 --> 01:03:40,316
Well, there you have it.

1038
01:03:40,349 --> 01:03:41,617
You should probably hurry up

1039
01:03:41,651 --> 01:03:44,320
and begin your escape as well. [groans]

1040
01:03:44,353 --> 01:03:45,588
Shoyo, are you okay?

1041
01:03:47,256 --> 01:03:48,624
It's ironic, isn't it?

1042
01:03:49,659 --> 01:03:52,562
I've been full of hate for all my eternal life,

1043
01:03:52,595 --> 01:03:54,964
but now time is not on my side.

1044
01:03:56,365 --> 01:04:00,970
That boy...that boy granted me what little life I have left.

1045
01:04:01,504 --> 01:04:03,306
A path has been paved to the future.

1046
01:04:03,539 --> 01:04:06,008
[energy whooshing]

1047
01:04:07,076 --> 01:04:10,112
You are that future, and it's my job to protect you.

1048
01:04:14,951 --> 01:04:17,019
[rumbling]

1049
01:04:24,727 --> 01:04:26,996
[door shuts]

1050
01:04:30,233 --> 01:04:32,969
I must last, every second counts.

1051
01:04:33,703 --> 01:04:35,371
[Shinpachi] Mere seconds won't be enough.

1052
01:04:37,473 --> 01:04:39,275
If we were to add up all our lives,

1053
01:04:39,308 --> 01:04:40,209
